#: application/views/scripts/articles/september-2005-training-camp-summary.phtml:7
msgid "Hakuho Ryu Montreal was greatly honored with the opportunity to host it's first international training camp under the guidance and teachings of Okabayashi Shogen Sensei, founder and headmaster of Hakuho Ryu Aiki Budo. A number of participants from abroad were in attendance for the training camp."
msgstr "Le Hakuho Ryu de Montr&eacute;al fut tr&egrave;s honor&eacute; d'&ecirc;tre l'h&ocirc;te de son premier camp d'entra&icirc;nement international, sous la direction et les enseignements d'Okabayashi Shogen Sensei, fondateur et directeur du Hakuho Ryu Aiki Budo. Un grand nombre de participants venus de l'ext&eacute;rieur y assist&egrave;rent."

#: application/views/scripts/articles/september-2005-training-camp-summary.phtml:23
msgid ""
"Okabayashi Sensei concentrated his teachings on Aiki , how to use it and apply it in techniques from basic to advanced.\n"
"    The most important gift being that he taught us how to move.I want to take this opportunity to thank everyone who took\n"
"    time out of their schedules to make the sometimes very long trip to Montreal to be present at this camp. The true goal\n"
"    of this camp was to bring as many people in the the organization together as possible and to get to know each other better\n"
"    and I think that that goal was greatly accomplished thanks to the contributions of all."
msgstr "Okabayashi Sensei concentra ses enseignements sur l'aiki, comment l'employer dans les techniques de plus simples aux plus avanc&eacute;es.  La chose la plus importante qu'il nous enseigna est comment bouger.  J'aimerais profiter de cette occasion pour remercier tous ceux qui ont pris le temps &agrave; nous aider &agrave; faire de notre camp un grand succ&egrave;s.  Le but de ce camp &eacute;tait de rassembler autant de membres possibles de l'organisation, et d'apprendre &agrave; nous conna&icirc;tre davantage.  Je crois sinc&egrave;rement que cet objectif a &eacute;t&eacute; r&eacute;alis&eacute; et cela gr&acirc;ce &agrave; la contribution de chacun."

#: application/views/scripts/articles/september-2005-training-camp-summary.phtml:31
msgid "Daito Ryu Seminar a success in Italy"
msgstr "Succ&egrave;s du s&eacute;minaire de Daito Ryu en Italie"

#: application/views/scripts/articles/september-2005-training-camp-summary.phtml:32
msgid "summary provided by Mr. James Mullins"
msgstr "Sommaire fourni par M. James Mullins"

#: application/views/scripts/articles/september-2005-training-camp-summary.phtml:33
msgid ""
"Sensei began the seminar with a focus on the Aiki no Jutsu techniques\n"
"            of Daito Ryu. Various techniques were delved into for two hours. Sensei\n"
"            explained how successful performance of these techniques requires\n"
"            more of a focus on gravity and body movements, rather than strength.\n"
"            Then, during a break, some participants inquired about nikkajo techniques,\n"
"            so Sensei transitioned into some tachiai and ushiro techniques from\n"
"            the nikkajo. These were practiced for another two hours. As the 'flavor'\n"
"            of Aiki no Jutsu techniques and nikkajo techniques differ, all participants\n"
"            were able to practice two completely different sets of Daito Ryu techniques.\n"
"            After the seminar, Sensei was presented with a plaque of appreciation\n"
"            from Maestro Rocco LaGuardia of Taranto."
msgstr "Sensei d&eacute;buta le s&eacute;minaire en se concentrant sur les techniques d'Aiki no Jutsu techniques du  Daito Ryu. Plusieurs techniques furent explor&eacute;es pendant deux heures.  Sensei nous expliqua en quoi la r&eacute;ussite de ces techniques n&eacute;cessite davantage de concentration de l'esprit et des mouvements corporals que de force physique.  Puis, au cours d'une pause, certains participants s'inform&egrave;rent sur des techniques de la s&eacute;rie nikkajo, donc Sensei d&eacute;cida de pr&eacute;senter des techniques tachiai et ushiro de la s&eacute;rie nikkajo. Elles furent pratiqu&eacute;es pendant un autre deux heures.  Comme la 'saveur' des techniques d'Aiki no Jutsu et de nikkajo diff&egrave;rent, tous nles participants purent pratiquer deux s&eacute;ries compl&egrave;tement diff&eacute;rentes de techniques de Daito-ryu.  Apr&egrave;s le s&eacute;minaire, on pr&eacute;senta &agrave; Sensei un certificat d'appr&eacute;ciation de la part de Maestro Rocco LaGuardia de Taranto."

